author: NewsWire
title: Floyd Mayweather will soon get replacement for his burnt Jeep
text:
0 0 0 0 0 
Washington D.C., Oct. 12(ANI): Seems like Floyd Mayweather is done with mourning the death of his custom Jeep that got burned to death as he has got an even pimper version of the car on the way. 
Previously, it was revealed that the 38-year-old boxer lost four car in a trailer fire in Arizona including two Rolls-Royces, a Bentley and the brand new Jeep, he picked up in Miami back in July, reports TMZ.com. 
However, the owner of the auto firm in Miami has revealed that he is already working on custom Avorza Jeep for Mayweather. (ANI) Related Posts
